This paper deals with the analysis of simple games, which are a well-studied topic in computational game theory (cs.GT) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The concept of critical threshold value is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), as it is related to the stability and convergence of algorithms. Finally, the use of partitions and subsets suggests a connection to set theory and discrete mathematics (cs.SI).
